session.datatype
Class DatatypeFactory

java.lang.Object
  session.datatype.DatatypeFactory

public class DatatypeFactory
extends java.lang.Object

Instantiates a specified datatype implementation at this session handler location. This interface provides methods for creating remote instances of Datatype objects. In particular, an implementation of this interface should be used by a RemoteInstantiator implementation in order to allow that instantiator to ask for the creation of a new instance of a given model implementation.

When a datatype implementation is instantiated by an object implementing this interface, then a stub and an invoker class files for remote Datatype objects from the names of compiled Java classes are generated.

All of its remote methods throw the RemoteException for compatibility with Java's RMI framework.

public void recycle(Datatype data)
Releases a previously created Datatype object for further use. This avoids releasing it by the garbagge collector. Next calls to newInstance may return this released object.

Parameters:
